'''Critical Left''' (''Sinistra Critica'', SC) is a [[communism|communist]] [[List of political parties in Italy|political party in Italy]]. 

Originally a [[Trotskyism|Trotskyist]] faction within the [[Communist Refoundation Party]] (PRC), it broke ranks on 8 December 2007 to become an independent political party.<ref>http://www.agi.it/italy/news/200711281848-pol-ren0069-art.html</ref> From 2006 to 2008 SC had a member of the [[Italian Chamber of Deputies|deputy]], [[Salvatore Cannav<U+00F2>]], and a [[Italian Senate|senator]], [[Franco Turigliatto]]. Both voted consistently against the [[Prodi II Cabinet]] and the latter was responsible of the first major crisis of the government on 22 February 2007.<ref>http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/2007/febbraio/22/Governo_sotto_Prodi_dimette_Quirinale_co_9_070222001.shtml</ref> After this Turigliatto was expelled from the PRC in March.<ref>http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/2007/marzo/02/Turigliatto_fuori_dal_Prc_messi_co_9_070302164.shtml</ref> 

In the [[Italian general election, 2008|2008 general election]] SC ran its own lists and [[Flavia D'Angeli]] was chosen as candidate for Prime Minister of the party. In the election SC gained 0.5% of the national vote.

==Leadership==
*Spokesperson: [[Salvatore Cannav<U+00F2>]] (2007<U+2013>...), [[Flavia D'Angeli]] (2008<U+2013>...)

